<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Speaking as a lvl 57 Mage....I can't solo for **** right now....while a well equipped melee can<P>so this is the current situation I have....I have melees soloing the same spawns faster then me with less downtime...and I get a 50% exp penalty ontop of that....how cute<P>I do get around the exp penalty by chaining pets most of the time...sometimes by outnuking...it is NEVER mana effecient to equip a pet well and let it take 50% exp<P>As a mage....I am penalized threefold for having the best pets in the game...<P>1. The pet takes 50% exp if it does more damage then me<P>2. I give up the chance of ever having ANY defensive spells at all<P>3. My pet and lifeblood is not always out....when I travel I am open to death by whatever happens across me<P>onto number 3 I will also lump pet pathing...while it is not designed as a penalty...it most certainly must be considered because it is not going to be fixed anytime soon...and it most certainly is horrible...I've had pets run off and bring tons of fun back....I've had pets stand 3 feet away from me not fighting a thing and watch me die<P>So why are magicians penalized so heavily for something that in the late 50's doesnt even give me the power of a well equiped melee?<P>I see 2 solutions either would work<P>1. Lower the penalties for having a good pet<P>2. make our pets better<P><BR>its that simple<P>and pet stealing exp in a group is NOT an issue in most normal groups...a pet will never outdamage melee...no worries there
</FONT>
