<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I will probably be hated for this, but here are my opinions:<P>Beastlords solo amazingly well.  I am a 51st level troll beastlord.  I have never been powerleveled or twinked.  Even counting my experience penalty for being a troll *and* the 50% penalty I took while soloing (I almost never out-damaged my warder), I zoomed through the levels faster than anyone else in my guild.  Faster than I did with a necromancer.<P>Part of that could be because I'm a fairly experienced player, but the fact remains that I was able to solo better than I did when I played a necromancer, generally considered one of the "best" solo classes.<P>Post-50, however, remains to be seen.  I'm still doing ok against low-range dark blues while soloing for xp, but I don't know how far that will continue as I work my way to 60.<P>In short, I see no problem with the 50% xp penalty when soloing.  Even with it I leveled so quickly that my friends were amazed and joked about it. When I was 44th level one guildmember left EQ for a week and told me before she left "Now don't you be 50 when I get back!"  Sure enough, six days later I was 50.  That was mostly soloing or duoing with a druid or another beastlord.<P>As for the pet taking a share of the xp in groups... I'm still unclear on how *much* of a share they take when they do more damage than anyone else.  Do they take half of the total xp, leaving the remainder to be divided among the players?  Do they take an even share as though they were another player?  In the former case, that seems horribly unfair.  In the later, it seems absolutely fair.<BR> <IMG SRC="http://members.telocity.com/~Tipop2000/kraggan.jpg">
</FONT>
