Every time I see an non-issue like this, it burns me up! When I say 'non-issue' this is what I mean.<P>Ever since the beginning pets have 'absorbed' experience.  After three years of this I (and many others) have adjusted. My adjustment is some what radical...I dont give a fig about getting half or full exp!  That's right, could care less.  Here is why.  <P>I used to make <I>sure</I> that I did more than 50% of the damage to a mob!  In the end I was always sitting on my rump medding because MAGES ARE STILL THE ONLY PURE CASTER WITHOUT MANA REGENERATION!! (This is one of the true issues about the class, IMHO).  Somewhere along the line I discovered that if I simply nuked light blues twice with a medium range bolt (Scars at level 56) and dark blues with a medium range bolt (scars) and a high range DD (shock of blades) and then just sat down and let the pet (with damage shield on of course) wail away, I would have enough mana to take on <B>two more </B> mobs of any type before I would be force to med for 5-8 min. Where as making sure of my total experience I could only take on about 2 mobs in the same time span.<P>Hey sometimes I would get full exp, other times not.  I just continued to play.  This is all solo of course. I have NEVER been in a group where my pet did more than 50% damage except when it was a dire emergency and everyone was damn glad it did!<P>Having said that, I would of course <I>love</I> to have the penalty removed.  But of more importance is pathing issues, mana regen for mages (across ALL levels not just the +50 group), adding procs to our summoned weapons and armor (that's right PROCS!) or allowing mages to siphon various stats from our pets over time! (Yeah right, like <I>that</I> would ever happen!) <P>I have noticed over the past years that Verant would all ways pick out some post that would cover a topic they had already planned to 'improve' (read here throw out a bone to..) for casters, mages in particular  (can you say MODROD?) while they gloss over far more serious issues.  <IMG SRC="rolleyes.gif" border="0">
