I posted my own topic but I will put it here so that alan may read it!<P>I am lost for words after reading what Alan's wrote about pets!<P>From what I can work out he is basically saying that if a mage uses a pet and no one in the group does more direct damage than the pet then the pet will take the same amount of exp than a normal player would.<P>So this is how the game works!<P>Then fine, If a warrior does more damage then anyone single person in a group with a sword then the sword will take an equal share of the exp from the mob!<P>The sword is adding extra damage to each hit over what a warrior would normally do with his bare fists.<BR> <BR>How can I put this in such a simple form: <P>Oh I know<P>Magician + Pet = Warrior + Sword<P>Magician Minus pet = Warrior using no weapon<P>Pet = Weapon<P>Pet = Spell<P>Pet is the major part of a mages damage output, the same as a wizards using a large range of heavy nukes or a necromancers using a variet of Dots and Lifetaps.<P>I think alan is Confused beacuse we have nukes and a Pet, he takes the pet away and thinks of it as some extra tank that isnt absolutly needed by the mage to fight!<P>There is an old saying:<P>It is better to remain silent and be thought a Fool than to open your mouth and remove all doubt.<P>--------------------<P>Fear me for I have become Death, the destroyer of worlds and Consumer of life.
