if the classes are ballanced, there should be NO expp penalties in any part of the game.<P>the entire concept of applying an exp penalty to begin with was to cost certain players with certain abilities more time to gain experience. if the game was loaded with new players, there might be a need for this, but as most low lvl players are now twinks, the penalty is not fair to thoses that have them. <P>the fastest lvling character in the game now is not a pet class, or a race with regen, the fastest lvling class in the game is the class that has the best twink gear. period.<P>the exp penalties are an antiquated system that no longer serves that which it was creasted for. do away with them all together. i mean really, what advantage does a troll, iksar warrior have over a warrior that starts out at lvl 1 with over 600 hitpoints, a weapon over .5 on the damage ratio, and ac to  match. or better yet, what advantage does any class have compared to a player with a high lvl druid/shamy/cleric standing behind them on another acct.<P>the only thing exp penalties do any more is PUNNISH NEW PLAYERS. do away with them alltogether.<P>that said:<P>soloing,<BR> of the three pet classes, mage/necro/bst, mages solo the worst. atleast give them a break. and if you insist on punnishing pet classes for soloing easier, you should also attach a exp penalty on snare for druids. do away with them.<P>grouping, <BR>the pet IS the reason you invite a necro or beastlord in a exp group. mages atleast have a good dd line as dd lines go. many times i am in groups with my necro that dont have a well ballanced group. many times i end up with a lower lvl melee class or a bard even as the tank. many times the melee cant taunt the mob off my pet even with the taunt turned off. infact, necros are doomed to unballanced groups thanks to you guys already, pets should get NO experience in a group EVER.<P>exp penalties for pets and regen and a little more hp or str is no longer justified. they just hurt the players with the least resources, basiclally new players. and just incase you guys havent checked lately, you dont really have alot of those. so why punnish them before they even start playing?<P>that said, i personally think it is really lame to create a class with spacific abilities, then punnish them for having them. very very lame.<P>--------------------<P>Lebie of the Rathe
