<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
The pet experience penalties are a relic from a time in which pets were far more powerful than players.  When everyone wore minotaur axes (or the best of them with SSoY) pets were very powerful.  Then they had a nerf on pet power, which made them significantly less powerful.  I'm sure this was introduced similary, because people complained about necro and mage solo ability.  However, like the hybrid experience penalty, this is an outdated idea.  It needs to be removed, and it needs to be removed now.  I've never played a mage, and I can tell you for certain, I will be FAR more hesitant to let a mage in my group knowing he will siphon experience from the rest of us.  Even more experience if he is doing his job properly (read killing monsters).  I, for one, never thought mages were a "broken" class before, but now I agree with the rest of them.  Any time in which someone cannot find a group because of the inherent penalties that come with playing that class there is a problem.<BR>This is an issue that demands to be resolved.
