<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I think the common thought is - if a character is balanced with al lthe others, then the character should get the same xp as all the others.<BR>Now given that there is a level cap in the game, all characters MUST be balanced, otherwise some lvl 60 characters will be stronger than others, and that isnt fair.<BR>Much like the hybrids - originally designed to be more powerful because they were a caster warrior mix, wound up being balanced, and then finally having their XP penalty removed when someone twigged that that wasnt right.<BR>Basically, is a mage twice as strong with a pet as a warrior.  Nup.  No way.  Nada.<BR>I personally disagree with ANY XP penalty being in the game.  If for the same XP, one character is lvl 60, the other lvl 58, then the lvl 60 character is stuck, while the lvl 58 character can become more powerful still.<BR>But that believe of mine opens a whole big big big can of worms, better not to go there....<BR>This issue is contencious, but I dont know enough about high end pets (my SK never worries about being out done by his pet) to state a balanced fix, but my gut feeling is, raise the % mark at which a pet takes xp, perhaps to 60% plus 5% per person in the group.  How is that.<P>Have a nice day
