I have never played a pet class but I am going to haveto agree that pet taking 50% of experience is not at all fair.  Casters all have spells, by casting a pet spell they are simply using the tools given to them as a class.  I would compare this to giving an enchanter half as much experience if they used mezz, or giving a shaman half as much experience if they decided to use a DoT . . . the spells are there to be used and the downsides to each spell should balance its own merits . . . Especially with mages, pets are a class defining spell, and by penalizing them for using it would be like giving a cleric less experience for casting a heal during a fight.  With beastlords I feel there is an even further problem as it can be very very hard for them to outdamage their "pet" with their limited melee ability and weakened spell line.  If mages were given something valuable to a group other than their pets then they wouldn't need to solo where their pets will tend to outdamage them.
