I have a level 56 Magician.<P>What about the level difference between players in a group? If memory serves a lvl 40 can get exp with a lvl 60.  That widespread of a level difference is absurd for a serious exp group but not when you take into account groups of friends or guild members.  <P>In a regular exp group (say in Velks or Seb) you might have anyone from lvl 49 to 60 in the same group.  What about groups with an archmage and a bunch of low 50 melees?  The archmage might have the lvl 49 epic pet or Greater Vocaration Water rogue pet?  In cases like that, and none too hypothetical either, the pet has a chance to outdamage the melees AND I wouldn't say that there is a class balance issue.  6+ levels difference is a pretty big deal (why it just took me almost 3 months to do ONE level playing most days).<P>Does Verant really understand how anxious people can be about getting exp; or even much much worse, losing it?  I don't get that impression that they do.<P>I have seen sooo many times many lfg people ignored or refused an open position because that spot was being held open for someone who could make the exp flow a lot faster by cutting down on downtime and getting more pulls(principaly someone like a healer, buffer, or tank).<P>I have seen territorial arguments in many zones about pull rights esp. in crowded high exp zones (e.g. the famous Velketors /ooc Hey stop pulling our mobs Top is camped).<P>People disband pickup groups all the time because the pulls don't happen fast enough for them.<P>I have also seen friends (good people) get hotheaded and leave the group mad at each other because of harsh words due to disagreements over what will happen next on a corpse run gone bad (two or more deaths).<P>Dying for me means losing the exp it took 4 or 5 hours of playing to get (albeit I'll likely get most of it back with an exp rez but for a good bit of hard earned cash). <P>Now if people are told that a class with a pet that doesn't really have any useful or unique benefits to help reduce downtime BETWEEN fights like clarity, regen, and heal or to help with pull management like sow, mez, or harmony AND might actually reduce that potential precious exp; then you can DAMN well believe that they won't be high on anyone's list to fill open spots in a pick up group.<P>I play a mage.  I have a pet by design.  That's my gig.  Mage + Pet = 1 Character (Not 2!!!)  I'm sorry, but any other thought about that is WRONG as far as I'm concerned.<P>If a mage at a certain level has a pet that can outdamage an average equipped melee character of the SAME level then I can admit to a class balance issue.  Deal with THAT issue.  DON'T give me an experience penalty for a flaw in the game AND make it harder for me to get in a group.  That's actually a BAD solution.<P>Yes, a couple mages in the raid gimp group can help outdamage the KS group if they coordinated it, but Yes it also takes us 15 minutes to med - I timed it.<P>You talk about solo ability of a mage.  Let me tell you something about that.  I've done it before and it works ok (but just barely and it's slow and boring so I don't like doing it).<P>If I get a SINGLE add I die (mobs hit me and unless I run away or gate and zone I die).  I have to go someplace I am familiar with (which requires research and practice the latter of which sometimes requires deaths) so I can pull singles.<P>Then I have to get the best pet I can get.  Pets have a level ranges when summoned of like 4 or 5 levels.  I think that's enough to justify summoning and summoning until I get a pet that hits for max (highest level with more HP, AC, and damage).  This can take 15-20 minutes or more.<P>Then I have to summon stuff for the pet.  3 daggers for resists (primary, secondary, range), coldstone (for ammo first then neck for some AC), rings of levitation (more AC), elemental blanket, elemental defender, summoned plate armor all take a couple bubs of mana.  That's like 6 more minutes.<P>Then factor in a few more minutes after buffing the pet with the latest burnout and damage shields.<P>So all told, 20+ minutes after logging in I might be good to go to fight the FIRST mob(even after I get to camp spot).<P>Then I pull a decent blue mob and use half a bar of mana and get pet down to 50 health and wait 10 more minutes before pulling again.  A few more pulls and my personal buff shields wear off which is another bub and a half of mana (another 5 minutes of medding).<P>If I die or zone or if the pet dies I have to do all that again.  It's not worth it and we're not a great solo class but we CAN solo (did I mention that we will die WITH mana if even a couple GREEN adds join in because we can't cast spells).<P>I don't like the work around (reclaiming pet each fight) for soloing because it actually reduces our damage potential and having an exp penalty isn't fun.<P>Well that's my $10 worth.<P>Hope you've learned something.<P>- Caeadyen<BR>Lvl 56 Tunare Mage on Tunare
