</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Speaking as a L31 Mage, I'd say that a mage pet should get exp according to it's relative level and dmg dealt, not a flat 50% if it does the most vs 1% if I do.  Wouldn't make the PLers happy, but would make the run-of-the-mill mage happier.  The trade off still is the pet's dmg dealing outdoing the mage, but the relative exp loss would be more appropriate to mage pets being "party members".<P>Personally, as a mage who doesn't engage in the mad scramble for exp, the reduced exp from the pet outdoing me just gives me more time to accrue wealth and get my required skills up.<P>Another possibility is for the mage to get a bonus 10% exp (not extra share of same) if he/she uses a pet in a group, but still splits it with his/her pet accordingly (a sort of mini-group within a group).<P>just my 1/5 cp.<P>--------------------<P>Ogamol/Bloodshy<BR>Og Shm/DE Mag<BR>L21   /L31<BR>Solusek Ro
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
